    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sudden outbreaks of a disease in people, animals, or plant populations in a region where the disease was not previously recognized or where a rapid increase in the number of new cases of a previous existing endemic disease occurs in the area.</Note_Text>
